NCERT 11 - Indian Constitution at Work

Purpose - defines the structure of the government, lays down the rights and duties of citizens,
and provides a framework for governance.

Constitution - is to limits the power of the government, importance of democracy. Protects the freedom of the individual.

why do we need the constitution ? - framework for governance, limiting the power of rules against the citizens, protections for rights. - parliamentary form of government we have choices, supreme court is the guardian of the Constitution. Social contract.

